abstract: Perhaps no issue has divided the field of Democratic 2020 presidential hopefuls more than "Medicare for All."
snippet: Perhaps no issue has divided the field of Democratic 2020 presidential hopefuls more than "Medicare for All."
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Perhaps no issue has divided the field of Democratic 2020 presidential hopefuls more than "Medicare for All."
headline_main: Where Democratic Presidential Candidates Stand on 'Medicare for All'
headline_print_headline: Where Democratic Presidential Candidates Stand on 'Medicare for All'

abstract: Several candidates accused the Democratic National Committee of changing its qualification criteria to benefit Michael Bloomberg, who is not competing in the first four states.
snippet: Several candidates accused the Democratic National Committee of changing its qualification criteria to benefit Michael Bloomberg, who is not competing in the first four states.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — The Democratic National Committee released its latest debate qualification criteria on Friday, and as is tradition, some candidates think they’re unfair.
headline_main: Democrats criticize D.N.C. change to debate rules.

abstract: Inside the very weird homestretch in Iowa, where candidates were thin on the ground, but reporters were not.
snippet: Inside the very weird homestretch in Iowa, where candidates were thin on the ground, but reporters were not.
lead_paragraph: OTTUMWA, Iowa — As excellent as the Bernie Sanders event was — as excellent as it was to hear from the filmmaker Michael Moore and to eat Ben & Jerry’s ice cream scooped by the actual Ben and the actual Jerry, longtime Sanders supporters — it would have been even more excellent, was the general feeling, if Mr. Sanders himself had been able to come to Ottumwa.

abstract: In a private memo circulated to donors on Friday, the Biden campaign announced that it had hired Dave Huynh as the campaign’s delegate adviser.

lead_paragraph: NORTH LIBERTY — In a private memo circulated to donors on Friday, the Biden campaign announced that it had hired Dave Huynh as the campaign’s delegate adviser.

abstract: Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg contributed more than $200 million (£152.16 million) of his own money to his bid for the Democratic presidential nomination as of the end of 2019, according to disclosures his campaign filed on Friday with the Federal Election Commission.
snippet: Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg contributed more than $200 million (£152.16 million) of his own money to his bid for the Democratic presidential nomination as of the end of 2019, according to disclosures his campaign filed on Friday w...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg contributed more than $200 million (£152.16 million) of his own money to his bid for the Democratic presidential nomination as of the end of 2019, according to disclosures his campaign filed on Friday with the Federal Election Commission.
headline_main: U.S. Candidate Bloomberg Spent $200 Million of Own Wealth on Presidential Bid in 2019
headline_print_headline: U.S. Candidate Bloomberg Spent $200 Million of Own Wealth on Presidential Bid in 2019

abstract: Countering private campaign funding with public campaign funding is the most viable way to limit the political influence of the wealthy.
snippet: Countering private campaign funding with public campaign funding is the most viable way to limit the political influence of the wealthy.
lead_paragraph: There is a straight line from the Supreme Court’s 2010 decision in the Citizens United case to a dinner party the president attended at the Trump International Hotel in Washington in April 2018.

abstract: The Democratic Party on Friday announced new rules around how  presidential hopefuls can qualify to take part in debates,  changes likely to allow billionaire media mogul Michael Bloomberg to join the stage in February.
snippet: The Democratic Party on Friday announced new rules around how  presidential hopefuls can qualify to take part in debates,  changes likely to allow billionaire media mogul Michael Bloomberg to join the stage in February.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Democratic Party on Friday announced new rules around how presidential hopefuls can qualify to take part in debates, changes likely to allow billionaire media mogul Michael Bloomberg to join the stage in February.

lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont remains a financial powerhouse, and the two billionaires in the Democratic primary race are spending enormous amounts of money on their candidacies, according to new filings with the Federal Election Commission.
headline_main: A new picture of the Democratic money race.
